cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on natural language processing tasks such as abstractive summarization and question generation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new pre-training model and self-supervised objective. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a model that can plan for future tokens. The proposed n-stream self-attention mechanism could also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper involves natural language processing tasks, it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as text is a form of visual data.
